# LRP Phase 3 Marketing Sprint Loop

Use this loop when continuing Mortgage Readiness Partner Program (Phase 3) marketing kit work without waiting for manual "merge and continue" messages.

## When triggered

- User asks to complete / expand the Mortgage Partner Marketing Package, Phase 3 kit, or turnkey partner program
- User says merge and continue, execute next steps, keep moving, or similar
- Cursor Automation fires after a PR merges to `main`
- You detect `main` advanced since the last Phase 3 slice

## Loop steps (always in order)

1. **Sync** — `git checkout main && git pull origin main`
2. **Scope** — pick the next unchecked slice from [`docs/lrp-enterprise/build-bible/volumes/07-marketing-launch/partner-kit/phase-3/00-completion-checklist.md`](../../docs/lrp-enterprise/build-bible/volumes/07-marketing-launch/partner-kit/phase-3/00-completion-checklist.md)
3. **Branch** — `git checkout -b feature/lrp-phase3-<short-name>` from synced `main`
4. **Implement** — claim-library-locked manuscripts/specs under `partner-kit/phase-3/`; update checklist status; link from Phase 3 README / Vol 07 when needed
5. **Verify** — markdown links resolve; no forbidden claims (guaranteed approval, fabricated FICO, unsupervised filing); brand name + tagline + disclaimer where public-facing
6. **Ship** — conventional commit, push, open PR to `main`
7. **Auto-merge** — after `gh pr create`, run:
   ```bash
   gh pr merge --auto --squash
   ```
8. **Continue** — do not stop for user input unless blocked; after merge, start step 1 again

## Slice sizing

- One major asset group per PR (e.g. sales folder, welcome packet, social pack batch, email audience batch)
- Prefer full manuscripts over outlines; expand Phase 1/2 stubs rather than duplicating conflicting copy
- Binary Canva/PPT/PDF press files stay external — ship specs + copy; place delivered binaries under `assets/lrp/` when available
- Follow [CLAIM-LIBRARY.md](../../docs/lrp-enterprise/build-bible/CLAIM-LIBRARY.md) and LRP structure rules

## GitHub CLI (Windows)

`C:\Program Files\GitHub CLI\gh.exe`

## Blockers — stop and report

- Ambiguous legal/compliance claim that needs counsel
- Request for real testimonials without signed releases (use fictional composites)
- Request to fork a separate Mortgage product codebase
